snippet.textDisplay: There are so many questions around what this song is about and what the lyrics mean. Tajdaar-e-Haram literally means the Crowned King of the Haram Mosque in Mecca, Saudi Arabia. This is a form of sufi music called 'Qawwali' which is sung in the praise of Prophet Muhammad (SAW). The lyrics cannot be literally explained in plain English, but they are written with love of epic proportions for the Prophet (SAW). Urdu speaking friends should not have a problem understanding most of it (but not all) and Hindi-speaking friends should get it more or less.
